snippet.title: Judas Priest - Painkiller (At The Pool Deck Karaoke On 70,000 Tons Of Metal)
snippet.description:

I spent my twenties with clenched fists, hell-bent on tearing the world apart‚Äîbut I never did.

I soon realized that to keep making music, passion alone wasn‚Äôt enough. I needed resources. I needed a way to survive.

Along the way, my body broke down, I took my hits, and I came dangerously close to losing the one person who mattered most. My thirties came at me like a storm, knocking me down with trials that left me in despair.

By the time another opportunity came, I had already lost much of my confidence.

So early last year, I hit the road‚Äînot just through cities, but through my own doubts‚Äîto reclaim what was mine and redefine myself once more.

And through it all, I found them. Friends who still believe in me. People who live and breathe my music.

An imperfect stage. The fear of standing unprepared.
A moment where all I had was my voice.

I know this is just karaoke. But for me, it‚Äôs more than that. It‚Äôs a turning point‚Äîone I refuse to ignore.

And now, I‚Äôm ready for the next round.
